# Skill-first workflow

Before starting any task, quickly review the available Agent Skills in the workspace (and any globally available skills) and decide whether a relevant skill applies.

## Required behavior

- If the task matches a skill’s stated “Use when”, follow that skill’s instructions as the preferred approach.
- If multiple skills could apply, pick the most specific one (task-specific beats general).
- If a skill requires reading a `SKILL.md` first, do that before proceeding.
- If no relevant skill exists, proceed normally but keep the skill list in mind as the task evolves.

## Practical checklist (do this at the start)

- Scan `skills/` for available skill folders (and any known global skills).
- Select applicable skill(s) based on the user request.
- Apply the chosen skill’s workflow; avoid reinventing its process.

